                        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-700 leading-relaxed font-medium" id="quick-answer">
                            A comforter is a single piece of bedding with a built-in fill, while a duvet consists of a
                            separate insert and a removable cover, which makes the cover easier to wash frequently.
                        </p>
                        <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-slate-100 flex items-center justify-between">
